  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026q1",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this gap is accepted because (a) all quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) are met for all three primary QoIs, (b) the single test condition is directly representative of the regulatory submission scenario, and (c) additional test conditions are planned for the next validation cycle. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support submission of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Note: the material property and bench test datasets predate the current model revision date (2026-02-14); re-validation of these datasets against the updated model build is planned for Q2 2026.",
